http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/kozhikode/%E2%80%98Invoke-anti-corruption-Act%E2%80%99/article14026566.ece

Welcoming the order of Thrissur Vigilance Court to register a First Information Report (FIR) against Chief Minister Oommen Chandy and Electricity Minister Aryadan Mohammed, CPI(M) Polit Bureau member Pinarayi Vijayan has said that both Mr. Chandy and Mr. Aryadan should be subjected to criminal proceedings as per anti-corruption laws.Talking to media persons at Ottappalam and Mannarkkad here, Mr. Vijayan demanded action under the same law against Congress leader Thampanoor Ravi, who allegedly put pressure on solar scam accused Saritha S. Nair to make statements favouring Mr. Chandy.